{"TopicId":154566,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Why do unpowered illuminators change state?","CreatedByName":"klond","CreatedById":38787,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-06T02:27:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"klond","CreatedById":38787,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-06T02:27:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothesis\u003C/strong\u003E: undocking test vehicle with battery\u00A0should removed power to lit stationary illuminator. \u00A0Re-docking (reconnecting the battery) should re-light it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ETest\u003C/strong\u003E: I\u00A0built a sample on/off switch. \u00A0The\u00A0unit splits into 2 vehicles, battery-side swingarm and lamp-side post.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gWKf6hD.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/gWKf6hD.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022zPadDGD.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/zPadDGD.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00227LO49aT.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/7LO49aT.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EConclusion\u003C/strong\u003E: Illuminators don\u0027t hold their ON state when they lose electricity via undocking (even with probe core attached). \u00A0I prefered they keep the state I set. \u00A0BOO! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-06T02:29:02Z\u0022 title=\u002201/06/2017 02:29  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 6, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by klond\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-06T04:47:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Suggestions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"John FX","CreatedById":59415,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-06T11:10:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPersonally I would regard this as a bug and report it on the bugtracker.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}